text: UPDATE... I've been using this app for over a year and it's just gets better. And it has made a difference in my life normally I use it first thing to start my day but sometimes if I need time out it's what I use. My stress levels are very low now... Thank you for the app   One of the best I have tried cannot decided on the yearly subscription would prefer a one-off payment. I did it yearly subscription unlocks so much more. Life is a lot better for mediation and this app is brilliant at getting me to that every day.

I think this is a very nice app. Sadly 90% of what's offered , you have to purchase. I tried multiple "free" meditations only to come back for day 2 and discover they were now locked and I was redirected to a page that said I now had to pay for it, even though the day before it was free. The fee for the subscription content offered is too high. After listening to the multiple meditations I was actually able to listen to (for a day) they all began to sound the same. Excellent idea for an app but needs more variety.

I've been using this app pretty much daily for nearly a year. I feel this app has helped me become a calmer person. I love that I can choose different meditations for a surprising number of different moods. The voice is always the same person and is very soothing and the messages imparted are clear and insightful. It's a little more expensive to subscribe than I was expecting, but ultimately worth it.

Fix the open ended meditation! It did not work at all! Love the app, however the open ended meditation with the bells needs to be fixed. The open ended meditation is more broken than I thought. There's no rhyme or reason as to why it randomly stops working in the middle of a session. I have tried everything. Leaving the screen on, turning off do not disturb and using headphones but it still works inconsistently. Please fix this!

A large variety of lesson topics available! Lessons for focus, sleep, gratitude, happiness, calm, relationships, and soooo much more! Or you can listen to stories for sleep, follow a guided meditation, listen to a master class, listen to your choice (of many!) of ambient noise, listen to music to help focus or relax. This app is so comprehensive, it would be surprising if you didn't find something in here to enhance your well-being.

Previously was a wonderful app. Overnight with an update, the meditations I frequently used are now paid only - they were free for years. Due to the overnight change I am retracting my 5 star rating and replacing it with a 1 star rating. Instead of buying the app, I will search for others. This is everything I had wanted

Used to be great and they had a few basic guided meditations for free, now everything's behind a pay all including the stuff that used to be free. Luckily the tracks were just audio files that I managed to extract and can play on an audio app. Will probably delete the app soon if content remains behind a pay wall.

I used to LOVE this app. I've been using it for years and had grown quite addicted to it. However, this last update has changed all my favorite meditations routines to PAID ONLY. They used to be free (for years) but overnight suddenly we have to pay.  Guess what? Your scheme had the opposite effect on me, I'm going to find another app rather than pay you for what used to be free.

Meditation had become a part of my daily routine.  Calm helps me every day.  Some of the sessions bother me because the older sessions have a somewhat harsh voice.  But all of the newer modules with the newer voice is much more soothing.  Edit: seems like they are phasing out the older sessions.  I love the new open ended sessions as well.

I used to love this app. All my favorite meditations were free but now they're all suddenly paid. Seems like they're trying to convert most to paid and put limitations of whatever free stuff that is left over. I can't afford another subscription service. I'm going to look for a new app.

I've struggled with meditation my whole life. It's something that I was always told would do me good but it was never possible. Now thanks to this, not only am I meditating but I'm noticing a general Improvement in My overall well-being. I love everything about this app and what their team has done

I love this app. I was very sceptical about meditation, but am now converted. The app looks beautiful & sounds beautiful. As previous reviewers have mentioned Tamara Levitt's voice is amazing; I start to relax as soon as she starts speaking. The sleep stories are wonderful, although I've never managed to hear the end of one as I'm sound asleep. I'm not a particularly stressed or anxious person, but I still find I feel better after a meditation session; more relaxed, happier & looser limbed. The lessons learned during meditation can be applied to many areas of life & I think I'll be a better, nicer & more patient person if I continue to use & learn from this app. I highly recommend that you give it a go. If you don't find any benefits just uninstall it. No harm, no foul.

I used to love this app, and I've recommended it for so many people - it's definitely been 5 stars. However, they've now changes it so there are no longer any free guided sessions. Disappointing that I now have to uninstall and look for a new meditation app :(

Great app! It keeps my meditation on schedule and so easy to use. I love the open-ended meditation, and ones with the guidance as much. I'm thinking about getting premium, but there are issues and people complaining about it so I stick to the free acc. But please work on the premium.

Its amazing in pre demo for the one meditation it gives you free. Although if you have the cash and can justify a monthly payment its probably way better. Still good as background sounds to complement a byo meditation though. Stories were the only part that i thought were a little creepy

I'd love to give 5 stars, but it keeps messing up my progress. At the end of the day when I'd like to continue with the next lesson, I see that I'm stuck on the previous one I completed the day before. Happens all the time. It ruins the otherwise perfect experience I'm having with the app.

This app gave a nice selection in the free version. It was enough for me to decide to pay $60 for a year. 7 Days of Calming Anxiety is a great series.  I look forward to the calming sessions. There is so much meditation content in the full app, that I will never get bored or run out of material. The music selection could be improved.

Great app. All the programs are really good. The only thing I'd want is for the 'returning to now' meditations to not have any guidance beyond an intro. There's way too much talking in that one, but the bell is helpful.

I have used sleeping tablets for years.. when I heard about this I thought yeah right ... well I haven't taken a sleeping tablet since that first night, sleep like a baby. Highly recommend to anyone looking for a good night's sleep and waking up feeling refreshed and happy!  Awesome

Based on previous reviews, I purchased the yearly subscription. I'm so glad I did. I'm enjoying the sleep stories at night to help calm my mind before I fall asleep. I find myself looking forward to waking up so I can do my 10 minute guided meditation every morning. It helps set the intention for my day along with writing in a gratitude journal for 5 minutes. I've been faithfully meditating with the app every day for 2 weeks and can already see a change in my mood and positivity. I'm also able to handle minor irritations much better. Do something good for yourself and get this app!

A really nice app with a good content, but surprised to see that after my yearly subscription ended the price went up from 43 to over 100 euro per month which i find sad, if the purpose was really to help people. Besides the fact that the new prices are a bit extreme but there are also other apps. So i guess time to change. But thanks for the nice content till now.

I think the app is good. But you're only allowed to listen to a couple of free samples. Then they want for you to pay a monthly fee or one time fee which is way too expensive if they charge like a one time fee of like $0.99 then it would be worth it.

This app breaks my heart. I LOVE every single free guided meditation, but sadly there are about 10 of them. This app helped me to get through some tough times, but I had to repeat "7 days of Calm" a couple of times. The price for subscription is ridiculously high, I definitely can't afford this.

I was loving this app. But I feel there should be more free guided meditation. What was once free isnt and I will probably stop using the app because of this. If you made it to where you can purchase things individually at a time instead of the monthly or yearly price I would spend money on it.

There used to be a lot more free guided meditation packages last year and I did purchase the full year at the time and loved it. I haven't renewed this year though partly due to the cost and I'm a little disappointed that many of the previous free sessions are now pay only.
Used to love doing the body scan mediation which was free now have to pay a too high price to unlock everything. Deleting the app and finding something else now. Greed is a pitiful place to be

rerecord the field of grain. theres a motorbike noise in it.  Sleep stories are great.  If you really have got a bad case of hubris and are charging like wounded bulls like the recent reviews say i may have to reconsider my renewal. Pity.

I like this app. The body scan meditation used to have me drifting off to sleep in no time - wonderful! But I preferred the older versions with the softer voice - the current voice is too harsh for me. Could there be an option to choose different voices according to taste? It's a shame the older content like the body scan has become paid content - this was the one I liked best. Perhaps there could be a cheaper one-off payment option to unlock specific items rather than a regular subscription?

This app really helps me sleep and deal with my anxiety in stressful situations, along with helping my sleeping problems because I get to anxious at the end of the night before bed. It helps me become calm and level headed, and also teaches me ways to stop having a negative attitude towards everything. Love the music for sleep. Wish I could connect the app through my Alexa. But otherwise I love this app and the premium features.

On the surface,  its a great app.  The background ambience and the guided meditations are a wonderful idea. Unfortunately,  80-90% of the content is locked, and even the seemingly unlocked content only let's you try day 1 before you have to pay. To make matters worse, the app  seems to be stuck for me,  never letting me progress past day 3 of the basic meditation package.  I don't want to drop money on the app if it turns out this is true for every package.

I really have enjoyed this app. I really wish there was a cheaper light version. Or a limited $20-30 for life option, for people who hate committing to subscriptions. Other than that the free option is very good. I would be willing to pay a little for an upgrade but not subscribe, so I guess I'll go for the free option.

I had a huge anxiety problem last year. This app really helped pull me through. I stopped meditating for a couple weeks and came back and my 2 most used meditations were locked. Overall I love the app, the instructors voice is perfect, but now the only things you ding have to pay for are the first days in a 7 or 21 day program. If you're ok with buying a subscription, this app is wonderful. But if you're like me and can't, don't bother. There's barely anything to listen to anymore.

I love this app. I have insomnia and this app has been great for helping that. There are so many different options from bedtime stories, to meditations to help with different areas like focus, sleep, college students, etc. Plus the background noise has helped me when I've been studying. Being someone who has a mind that is scattered, I'm so thankful that I found this app.
Love this app, I mostly use it for the thunder background scene tho. But I'm not for sure if I'm seeing things or going coocoo... $299.99 to unlock the premium for life? Isn't that a bit.. much?

I use the sleep stories to unwind and fall asleep.  Really wish there were more available either free or to but individually. Saying that I have yet to listen to the end of Blue Gold without being asleep. That one definitely works.

I honestly downloaded this app on a whim, and it definitely helped me become aware of anxiety that I didn't even know that I had. The meditations are extremely valuable and allowed me to feel calm and relaxed, which is a feeling I had apparently forgotten. Worth the download
On the first use this app has helped me with my anxiety. Thank to the team who put this together, if could afford it I would gladly pay for it.

Skeptical at first and a true believer now.  Every night I use a meditation session and a sleep story.  It has been two weeks and I noticed I sleep better and wake up easier! Usually I was so tired in the morning but this program is making a difference. REQUEST: I am a teacher and every morning I start my 4th graders off with morning mindfulness.  I have been just finding stuff for their age on YouTube,  but I would love for you to make a classroom series option please!!!!!!!  We would need at most 6 minute sessions since the school day is so restriced....PLEASE!!! :-)

E help me to deal with anxiety and a recent break on my relationship. I suffering to deal with all this by myself but the app is great. I wish I could a afford the whole year signature, but unfortunately I'm unemployed right now.

I was in a pretty dark place, new move feeling alone, unwelcome, and very upset. This not only helped destress my life, make me appreciate what I do have, and help me sleep, but also gently guided me to self esteem and improved my outlook on life. I really don't think I would have been able to stay sane without this app. Update: I just completed my 445 day in a row, still love it, still need it.
